"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347668","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2015-06-04","<p>The Electoral Commission recently published data relating to the 2015 UK Parliamentary general election results on its website. The requested information is set out in the attached table.</p><p>These results should be treated as provisional as they are based on data collected separately by the BBC, ITV, Sky News, and the Press Association. The Commission will publish a range of data for the 2015 UK Parliamentary general election in its report on the administration of those elections this summer. This will include the verified electorate figures by parliamentary constituency.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2015-06-04T09:53:33.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347668/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347668/answer","Electorate Data - Consitutencies with Electorates 10 Per Cent Higher or Lower than UK Average.docx","Electorate Data - Consitutencies with Electorates 10 Per Cent Higher or Lower than UK Average.docx","Constituencies 10% outside the UK average","Constituencies 10% outside the UK average","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347668/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2015-06-01","Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, which parliamentary constituencies have electorates more than 10 per cent (a) greater and (b) smaller than the UK average.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347669","Department for Education","false","2015-06-04","<p>The letter referred to, dated 27 May, was received by the Department for Education on 3 June and we intend to respond as soon as possible. The department aims to respond to correspondence we receive within 15 working days, in line with government standards.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have no plans to publish the letter, but the correspondent is free to do so should they wish.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","660","2015-06-04T15:26:48.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347669/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347669/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-01","Schools: St Ives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she expects to respond to the letter from Dorset County Council seeking to prevent St Ives School increasing its age range.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347670","Department for Education","false","2015-06-04","<p>The letter referred to, dated 27 May, was received by the Department for Education on 3 June and we intend to respond as soon as possible. The department aims to respond to correspondence we receive within 15 working days, in line with government standards.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have no plans to publish the letter, but the correspondent is free to do so should they wish.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","659","2015-06-04T15:26:48.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347670/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347670/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-01","Schools: St Ives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will place in the Library a copy of the letter from Dorset County Council seeking to prevent St Ives School increasing its age range.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347671","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Government has a clear mandate to improve Britain’s relationship with the rest of the EU, and to reform the EU so that it creates jobs and increases living standards for all its citizens. The Government will hold an in/out referendum on the UK’s membership of the EU by the end of 2017.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-08T15:02:06.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347671/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347671/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-01","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will commission an independent audit of the economic costs and benefits of UK membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347672","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-04","<p>The Department for Transport and Transport for London have respectively allocated £90m and £25m towards the electrification of the line (2013 prices).</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-04T11:44:42.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347672/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347672/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-01","Gospel Oak-Barking Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what funding has been allocated to Network Rail for the electrification of the Barking to Gospel Oak line.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347673","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-04","<p>Enabling works are due to commence in October 2015, with major on site works due to commence in June 2016. Passenger services on the electrified route are due to be available for use by passenger operators by 30 June 2017.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-04T12:11:26.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347673/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347673/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347673/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-01","Gospel Oak-Barking Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects work to (a) start and (b) be completed on the electrification of the Barking to Gospel Oak line.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347674","Home Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>Dungavel is the only immigration removal centre in Scotland. This question has been interpreted as relating to both Home Office and service provider staff. Information on the number of staff leaving the Home Office and service providers’ employment since 2006 is not held centrally. The reasons for leaving could only be provided by examination of individual records at disproportionate cost. Information on the amount of money spent on Home Office and service providers’ staff training and training provided to detainees since 2006 is not held centrally. Information is held in relation to incidents. There were no reported incidents for Home Office staff. The table below relates to health and safety incidents involving service provider staff. Major incidents are those that are reportable to the Health and Safety Executive. Management information is only available from 2009 in the following table.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","542 ; 543","2015-06-08T10:07:48.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347674/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347674/answer","Table of incidents 2009 to 2015 PQ 539[1].docx","Table of incidents 2009 to 2015 PQ 539[1].docx","Management information ","Management information ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347674/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-01","Detention Centres: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have left the employment of immigration centres in Scotland in each year since 2006; and for what reasons those people have left that employment.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347675","Home Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>Dungavel House in Strathaven, Lanarkshire is the sole immigration removal centre (IRC) located in Scotland.</p><p>The table below shows the number of people entering detention solely under Immigration Act powers at Dungavel House IRC from 2009 to 2014:</p><p>Year Detainees</p><p>2009 1,661</p><p>2010 1,432</p><p>2011 1,481</p><p>2012 1,431</p><p>2013 1,626</p><p>2014 1,297</p><p>Some detainees may be recorded more than once if, for example, the person has been detained on more than one occasion in the time period shown, such as a person who has left detention, but has subsequently been re-detained. Information on people entering detention prior to 2009 is unavailable.</p><p>The Home Office publishes quarterly and annual statistics on the number of people detained in the United Kingdom for immigration purposes, within the Immigration Statistics release. Data relating to people entering detention are available in tables dt_01 and dt_01_q in Immigration Statistics: January – March 2015 on the GOV.UK website: https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/home-office/series/immigration-statistics-quarterly-release and which will be placed in the Library of the House. Occupancy statistics were not collected by the Home Office before 2009 and figures prior to this are unavailable.</p><p>The following table shows the capacity of Dungavel House IRC from 2006 to 2015:</p><p>Year Capacity</p><p>2006 188</p><p>2007 188</p><p>2008 188</p><p>2009 190</p><p>2010 217</p><p>2011 217</p><p>2012 217</p><p>2013 217</p><p>2014 249</p><p>2015 249</p><p>The information provided in relation to capacity is based on management information only and has not been subject to the detailed checks that apply for National Statistics publications. These figures are provisional and are subject to change.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-06-08T10:11:38.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347675/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347675/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-01","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been detained in immigration removal centres in Scotland in each year since 2006; and what the capacity of such centres was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347676","Home Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>Dungavel House is the only immigration removal centre in Scotland. There have been no self inflicted deaths at the centre since 2006.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-06-08T10:07:24.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347676/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347676/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-01","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many detainees in immigration removal centres in Scotland have taken their own life since 2006.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","541"
