"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347437","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-05","<p>In March 2011 the Ministry of Defence Police (MDP) received an allegation of theft of artefacts from the sunken battlecruiser HMS Queen Mary. After due consideration it was concluded by the MDP that no further action could be taken. Any new information will be considered by the MDP in the normal manner.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-05T12:25:42.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347437/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347437/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-29","HMS Queen Mary: Salvage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to investigate allegations that the wreck of the battlecruiser HMS Queen Mary has been looted by salvors operating illegally.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347438","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-05","<p>One unsuccessful bidder complained and subsequently made a claim against the Department concerning a procurement undertaken in 2009, contract awarded on 8 January 2010. The Department has now entered into an out of court settlement for £15 million plus costs.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is currently carrying out a review of the conduct of the procurement exercise and the subsequent management of the contract to Odyssey Marine Exploration Inc. including the financial arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>The matter of whether any Departmental officials will be subject to disciplinary procedures is currently under consideration.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","513 ; 514 ; 515","2015-06-05T06:45:29.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347438/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347438/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-05-29","SS Gairsoppa: Salvage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what settlement his Department has arrived at with unsuccessful bidders for the salvage contract for SS Gairsoppa.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347439","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-05","<p>One unsuccessful bidder complained and subsequently made a claim against the Department concerning a procurement undertaken in 2009, contract awarded on 8 January 2010. The Department has now entered into an out of court settlement for £15 million plus costs.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is currently carrying out a review of the conduct of the procurement exercise and the subsequent management of the contract to Odyssey Marine Exploration Inc. including the financial arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>The matter of whether any Departmental officials will be subject to disciplinary procedures is currently under consideration.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","510 ; 514 ; 515","2015-06-05T06:45:30.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347439/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347439/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-05-29","SS Gairsoppa: Salvage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what complaints were received by his Department from unsuccessful bidders for the salvage contract for SS Gairsoppa.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347440","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-05","<p>One unsuccessful bidder complained and subsequently made a claim against the Department concerning a procurement undertaken in 2009, contract awarded on 8 January 2010. The Department has now entered into an out of court settlement for £15 million plus costs.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is currently carrying out a review of the conduct of the procurement exercise and the subsequent management of the contract to Odyssey Marine Exploration Inc. including the financial arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>The matter of whether any Departmental officials will be subject to disciplinary procedures is currently under consideration.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","510 ; 513 ; 515","2015-06-05T06:45:30.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347440/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347440/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-05-29","SS Gairsoppa: Salvage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether any officials in his Department have been subject to disciplinary procedures regarding the awarding and management of the salvage contract for SS Gairsoppa agreed between his Department and Odyssey Marine Exploration.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347441","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-05","<p>One unsuccessful bidder complained and subsequently made a claim against the Department concerning a procurement undertaken in 2009, contract awarded on 8 January 2010. The Department has now entered into an out of court settlement for £15 million plus costs.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is currently carrying out a review of the conduct of the procurement exercise and the subsequent management of the contract to Odyssey Marine Exploration Inc. including the financial arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>The matter of whether any Departmental officials will be subject to disciplinary procedures is currently under consideration.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","510 ; 513 ; 514","2015-06-05T06:45:30.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347441/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347441/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-05-29","SS Gairsoppa: Salvage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he has taken to recover outstanding money owed by Odyssey Marine Exploration to his Department regarding the salvage contract for SS Gairsoppa; and how much remains unpaid.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347442","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-03","<p>In the calendar year 2014, 792 households were accepted as owed a main homelessness duty to secure accommodation. These statistics are taken from the quarterly P1E forms completed by local authorities in England, which have been published at the following location;<br><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness</a>. <br><br>The homelessness legislation in England provides one of the strongest safety nets in the world for families with children and vulnerable people who become homeless through no fault of their own. Since 2010, the Government has invested over £500 million to prevent and tackle all forms of homelessness and this has helped local authorities prevent over 700,000 households from becoming homeless.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","488","2015-06-03T10:53:33.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347442/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347442/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-05-29","Housing: Southwark","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many households in the London Borough of Southwark applied for housing assistance under the homelessness legislation of the Housing Act 1996 in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347443","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-03","<p>This information is not held centrally. However, the English Housing Survey Headline Report, published on 25 February 2015, makes it clear that in most cases, it is the private rented tenant who chooses to end the tenancy.</p><p> </p><p>In 2013-14, 81% of private renters who had moved in the last three years, ended their previous private rented tenancy because they wanted to move; 7% were asked to leave by their landlord or agent; 10% of tenancies were ended by ‘mutual agreement’.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-03T10:57:37.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347443/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347443/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-05-29","Private Rented Housing: Southwark","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many households in the London Borough of Southwark were evicted from private rental accommodation in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347444","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-03","<p>Annual statistics on average house prices in the London Borough of Southwark are published in the Department's live tables 585 (mean) and 586 (median) which are available at the following link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-housing-market-and-house-prices" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-housing-market-and-house-prices</a></p><p> </p><p>Monthly statistics on the change in average house prices, at national and regional level, are published by the Office for National Statistics and are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/hpi/house-price-index/index.html" target="_blank">http://ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/hpi/house-price-index/index.html</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-03T10:56:34.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347444/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347444/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-05-29","Housing: Southwark","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the change in the average house price in the London Borough of Southwark in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347445","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-03","<p>Statistics on the private rental market in England and the London Borough of Southwark are published by the Valuation Office Agency and are available at the following link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/private-rental-market-statistics-may-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/private-rental-market-statistics-may-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>The Valuation Office Agency advises that because the composition of this sample changes over time, it is not possible to compare median rents provided in this publication with statistics in previous publications to infer trends in the rental market over time. The statistics therefore provide a snapshot that shows the range of rents across England.</p><p> </p><p>The official source on change over time in cost of renting is the Office for National Statistics Index of Private Housing Rental Prices available at the following link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/hpi/index-of-private-housing-rental-prices/january-to-march-2015-results/index.html" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/hpi/index-of-private-housing-rental-prices/january-to-march-2015-results/index.html</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-03T10:55:04.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347445/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347445/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-05-29","Private Rented Housing: Southwark","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the level of change in median monthly rent in the private sector in the London Borough of Southwark for (a) one, (b) two and (c) three-bedroom flats in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","487"
