 are registered at York College.</p><p>(4) Students registered at York Further Education College are only included in the data if they are studying a prescribed course of Higher Education.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information for the 2014/15 academic year will become available from the Higher Education Statistics Agency in January 2016.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","447","2015-06-03T13:38:52.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347303/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347303/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-05-28","Students: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what information his Department holds on the number of students at (a) St John's University, York, (b) the University of York and (c) York College.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347304","Department of Health","false","2015-06-05","<p>A list of the names and positons of all members of NHS England’s Clinical Priorities Advisory Group, Specialised Commissioning Oversight Group and Specialised Commissioning Committee has been attached to this answer.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-06-05T11:32:52.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347304/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347304/answer","CPAG membership list.docx","CPAG membership list.docx","NHS England's CPAG, SCOG & SCC membership list","NHS England's CPAG, SCOG & SCC membership list","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347304/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-05-28","NHS England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the (a) names and (b) positions are of all members of NHS England's (i) Clinical Priorities Advisory Group, (ii) Specialised Commissioning Oversight Group and (iii) Specialised Commissioning Committee.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347305","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-04","<p>A breakdown of the people who work in Defence Equipment and Support (DE&amp;S), including their grade and salary band, is published on the gov.uk website as part of the Government's Transparency Agenda at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/mod-roles-and-salaries-2014.</p><p>This organogram is updated twice per year and the latest publication reflects the position in DE&amp;S as at 30 September 2014. The next iteration, which will reflect the position as at 31 March 2015, is due to be published shortly.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-04T16:20:44.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347305/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347305/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-28","Chief of Defence Materiel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people of each grade and payroll cost work for the Chief of Defence Materiel.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347306","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-05","<p>Information on the number of people employed by the Department’s Head Office in each of the last five years and their salary band is provided in the attached document.</p><p> </p><p>We have interpreted Head Office to mean all civilian staff employed in the Head Office &amp; Corporate Services Business Area. This does not mean that all staff are stationed in London Headquarters (Main Building).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-05T13:54:41.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347306/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347306/answer","HOC360 Spread Sheet.xls","HOC360 Spread Sheet.xls","Ministry of Defence Head Office","Ministry of Defence Head Office","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347306/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-28","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people of each grade and payroll cost have been employed in his Department's Head Office in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347307","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-05","<p>For the purposes of answering this question I have taken operational base to be any RAF base that supports frontline operations, such as main operating bases and training establishments. There are 27 operational RAF bases in England: included in this are two RAF-named units operated by other Front Line Commands, and the tri-service technical training bases. There is one RAF base in Scotland and none in Northern Ireland. There are two RAF bases in Wales, which includes a technical training base. These figures do not include minor RAF units; RAF-operated diversionary airfields at Army units; sites operated by the United States Visiting Forces; sites only used by University Air Squadrons, Air Experience Flights, and Volunteer Glider Squadrons; Force Development Training Centres; Air Weapon Ranges; or remote radar and radio sites. There is one former RAF base in the UK that is in caretaker status, which is in England.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-05T12:26:46.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347307/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347307/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-28","Air Force: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many RAF bases in (a) England, (b) Scotland, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland are (i) operational and (ii) in caretaker status.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347308","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-02","<p>The Defence Board is composed of two Ministers, five senior officials and four non-executive directors, as follows:</p><p>Secretary of State for Defence, Rt Hon Michael Fallon MP;</p><p>Minister of State for Defence Procurement, Philip Dunne MP;</p><p>Permanent Under Secretary, Jon Thompson;</p><p>Chief of the Defence Staff, General Sir Nicholas Houghton;</p><p>Vice Chief of the Defence Staff, Air Chief Marshal Sir Stuart Peach;</p><p>Director General Finance, Louise Tulett;</p><p>Chief of Defence Materiel, Bernard Gray;</p><p>Lead Non Executive Director, Sir Gerry Grimstone;</p><p>Non Executive Director, Graham Williams;</p><p>Non Executive Director, Paul Skinner;</p><p>Non Executive Director, Danuta Gray.</p><p>The Defence Board last met on 28 May 2015 and will next meet on 26 June 2015. The Defence Board meets every month, except August.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-06-02T16:18:18.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347308/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347308/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-28","Defence Board","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the current composition is of the Defence Board; when it last met; when the next scheduled meeting is; and what the scheduled meeting programme is thereafter.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347309","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-04","<p>The Defence Reform report published in June 2011 was the result of the review led by the Defence Reform steering group, chaired by the noble Lord, Lord Levene. None of the steering group were paid for this task and the team supporting the review comprised staff reallocated from other duties at no additional cost to the Department beyond some £10,000 incurred on travel and subsistence.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-04T16:20:02.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347309/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347309/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-28","Defence Reform Review: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost to his Department was of the Defence Reform report, published in June 2011.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347310","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-04","<p>My right hon. friend, the Defence Secretary (Michael Fallon), released a written statement to the House on 17 December 2014 (Official Report, column 95ws) on Defence Reform: Review of Implementation, and placed a summary of progress against the Defence Reform recommendations in the Library of the House. I have attached an updated version of the summary. I will also place an updated copy in the Library as the version provided was found to have serial 12c missing in error.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-04T16:36:07.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347310/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347310/answer","20150601 53 recs table for PQ406(1).XLS ; 20141217 WMS - Defence Reform Review of Implementation.doc","20150601 53 recs table for PQ406(1).XLS ; 20141217 WMS - Defence Reform Review of Implementation.doc","406 - Recommendations of Defence Reform Report ; WMS Hansard Extract on Defence Reform","406 - Recommendations of Defence Reform Report ; WMS Hansard Extract on Defence Reform","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347310/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-28","Defence Reform Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many of the recommendations of the Defence Reform report, published in June 2011, have been successfully implemented.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347311","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-02","<p>The UK Government welcomes responsible foreign investment in the UK’s energy system. Specific proposals for ownership are assessed on competition grounds and against EU and UK law. All energy infrastructure in the UK must be operated in accordance with the relevant UK regulatory system.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-02T13:32:53.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347311/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347311/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-05-28","Energy: Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what her Department's policy is on the foreign ownership of (a) new nuclear reactors and (b) other new energy infrastructure in the UK.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347312","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-02","<p>Over the last 5 years DECC and Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (NDA) have published a number of documents related to plutonium disposition on the government’s and the NDA’s website, <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a> and <a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.nda.gov.uk</a> :</p><ul><li>Plutonium: Credible Options Technical Analysis – NDA - 30 January 2009</li><li>Plutonium: Credible Options Summary – NDA – 30 January 2009</li><li>Plutonium Credible Options Analysis (Gate A) – NDA – 07 December 2010</li><li>NDA Plutonium Current Position – NDA – 20 February 2011</li><li>Management of the UK’s Plutonium Stocks: A consultation on the long-term management of UK owned separated civil plutonium - DECC – February 2011</li><li>Management of the UK’s Plutonium Stocks: consultation response – DECC – December 2011</li><li>Proposals sought for alternatives to re-use of plutonium as MOX fuel – NDA – 23 February 2012</li><li>Progress on approaches to the management of separated plutonium position paper – NDA – 20 January 2014.</li></ul><p>Since January 2014, NDA have progressed work in line with the proposals outlined in its 2014 position paper. The Department expects the NDA to report later this year. NDA intend to publish a public position paper in due course summarising the outcome of the latest phase of work.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-02T16:18:05.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347312/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347312/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-05-28","Plutonium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what representations her Department has received from the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority on plutonium disposition in the last five years; and if she will publish the documents on that issue submitted to her Department in that period.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347313","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-02","<p>There is a significant opportunity in the UK nuclear sector for development of both the supply chain and skills capacity – it is estimated that an extra 30,000 people will be needed by 2021 to service the planned civil new nuclear build projects. Government is helping industry to realise these opportunities through initiatives such as the government-funded Nuclear Advanced Manufacturing Research Centre (NAMRC) and the Manufacturing Advisory Service (MAS), which have been established to support UK companies in accessing the market, winning business and growing capability.</p><p>In addition to nuclear, the Department is supporting a range of technologies in the renewables sector to develop further the UK’s low carbon economy and create a balanced and secure energy mix for the future. This is done by encouraging investment and working closely with industry to build a UK supply chain; we are world-leaders in offshore wind, with an industry that has attracted £9.5bn investment since 2010 and supports over 13,700 jobs. The renewable electricity sector supports around 110,000 jobs across the whole of the UK and could see a further £45bn private sector investment by 2020.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-02T16:17:33.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347313/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347313/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-05-28","Energy: Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will prioritise supply chains and the creation of jobs as close as possible to any future development of (a) nuclear infrastructure and (b) renewable energy sources.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347314","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-02","<p>There have been no meetings between my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, her Ministers or officials on the future of the Magnox site at Bradwell in the last three years.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-02T16:16:04.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347314/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347314/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-05-28","Bradwell Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what meetings (a) she, (b) Ministers in her Department and (c) officials in her Department have had on the future of the Magnox site at Bradwell in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347315","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-04","<p>The Royal Military Police made contact with the German authorities on three occasions in 2014 and five in 2015. In addition they met with the German authorities in 2012 and 2013 to discuss the case. The table below provides dates of the contacts with the German authorities in 2014 and 2015:</p><table><tbody><tr><td>2014</td><td>2015</td></tr><tr><td>16 July</td><td>5 January</td></tr><tr><td>21 October</td><td>8 January</td></tr><tr><td>20 November</td><td>21 April</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td>30 April</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td>6 May</td></tr></tbody></table><p>As the investigation is still under way it would not be helpful to speculate on when it might conclude. However Katrice’s family is being kept informed of any developments.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","330","2015-06-04T16:19:18.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347315/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347315/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-28","Katrice Lee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he expects Operation Bute to be concluded; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347316","Department for Education","false","2015-06-04","<p>The Department for Education procured the 2015-16 Special Educational Needs and Disabilities (SEND) delivery support contract through an open tender process.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The criteria for assessing bids are set out in pages 32-45 of the invitation to tender document, which can be found here: <a href="https://online.contractsfinder.businesslink.gov.uk/Common/View%20Notice.aspx?site=1000&amp;lang=en&amp;NoticeId=1611969" target="_blank">https://online.contractsfinder.businesslink.gov.uk/Common/View%20Notice.aspx?site=1000&amp;lang=en&amp;NoticeId=1611969</a></p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-06-04T16:48:39.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347316/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347316/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-05-28","Department for Education: Mott MacDonald","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 26 March 2015 to Question 228859 on special educational needs, what criteria her Department used to select Mott McDonald.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","332"
