"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346872","Home Office","false","2015-06-01","<p>The Portuguese approach to drugs was reviewed within ‘Drugs: International Comparators’ published in October 2014<em>.</em> The report is clear that the successes in Portugal cannot be attributed to decriminalisation alone. Whilst drug use went down and health outcomes improved, there was, at the same time, a significant investment in treatment.</p><p> </p><p>This Government has no intention of decriminalising drugs. The UK's approach on drugs remains clear: we must prevent drug use in our communities, help dependent individuals through treatment and wider recovery support, whilst ensuring law enforcement tackles the criminality that is associated with the drugs trade.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-01T09:39:23.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346872/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346872/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-05-27","Drugs: Decriminalisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent assessment she has made of the effects of the decriminalisation of drug use in Portugal on the prevalence of drug use in that country.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","93"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346873","Scotland Office","false","2015-06-02","<p>I have had no recent discussions on a UK withdrawal from the European Union, as this is not Government policy. The Government is focusing on renegotiation to reform the European Union and address the concerns of the British people about our membership.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-06-02T10:12:59.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346873/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346873/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-05-27","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had on the potential ramifications of a UK withdrawal from the EU on the Union.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","94"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346874","Prime Minister","false","2015-06-03","<p>Chequers, Chevening and Dorneywood are not owned by Government. They are administered by trustees in accordance with the terms of the individual trusts.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-06-03T14:44:01.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346874/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346874/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-05-27","Official Residences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will rent out (a) Chequers, (b) Chevening and (c) Dorneywood.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346875","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-03","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State does not plan to repeal the Infrastructure Planning (Radioactive Waste Geological Disposal Facilities) Order 2015, which brings development of geological disposal facilities, and the deep boreholes required to assess potential sites for these facilities, within the statutory definition of Nationally Significant Infrastructure Projects in the Planning Act 2008.</p><p>The Government believes that the Planning Act 2008 represents the most appropriate planning regime for infrastructure of this kind<em>.</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-03T13:33:42.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346875/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346875/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346875/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-05-27","Infrastructure: Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will take steps to repeal the Infrastructure Planning Standing Order.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346876","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-02","<p>The Government is committed to improving energy efficiency. Work on energy efficiency has been carried out across several directorates in the Department over recent years. Following an internal reorganisation within the Department earlier in 2015, the Energy Efficiency Deployment Office no longer exists. The work it previously carried out is now undertaken in a number of different directorates, including those focused on home energy use and business and local energy use.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-02T13:28:05.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346876/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346876/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346876/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-05-27","Energy Efficiency Deployment Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what her policy is on expanding the scope and budget of the Energy Efficiency Deployment Office; and how many staff are employed in that Office.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346877","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-04","<p>The detail of the arbitration mechanisms contained in the EU-US Free Trade Agreement (FTA) will be the result of on-going negotiations between the EU and the US.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Any arbitration conducted under the EU-US FTA would involve a fair and transparent procedure, with a range of public and private sector participants including, EU and Member States, investors and arbitrators, with all parties to the dispute able to appoint their own lawyers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Arbitration proceedings under an international investment treaty are typically carried out on an ad hoc basis, with the tribunal constituted solely for the purpose of resolving a single dispute. The costs of the arbitration are apportioned according to the arbitrators’ findings. Disputing parties may rely upon an international institution, such as the World Bank or the United Nations to provide the procedural rules for the tribunal. These services are provided on a non-profit basis.</p><p> </p><p />","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-04T13:13:29.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346877/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346877/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346877/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-05-27","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will make it his policy that the arbitration mechanism to be included in the proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership will not be carried out by a for-profit company.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346878","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-04","<p>The government will announce the detail and estimated Exchequer impacts of its plans to tackle tax evasion in the usual way, as part of the regular Budget and Spending Review processes.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-04T15:42:58.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346878/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346878/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-05-27","Tax Evasion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much additional revenue HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will recoup from new measures to reduce tax evasion by 2020; and what additional resources he plans to allocate HMRC to reduce tax evasion.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","90"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346879","Prime Minister","false","2015-06-03","<p>Appointments will be made in the usual way. Appointments will be vetted for propriety by the House of Lords Appointments Commission.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","518","2015-06-03T14:45:40.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346879/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346879/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-05-27","Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, by what formula will party political makeup of new appointments to the House of Lords be made over this Parliament.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346880","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-04","<p>The government’s long-term plan is working, restoring the public finances to a more sustainable path. The deficit has more than halved as a share of GDP from its post-war peak of 10.2% in 2009-10 to 4.8% by the end of last year. The latest data published jointly by the Office for National Statistics (ONS) and HM Treasury shows that public sector net borrowing for April 2015 is £6.8bn, down £2.5bn compared to the same time last year. But the job of fixing the public finances is not yet complete which is why we will continue with our plans to reduce the deficit further and build a more resilient British economy.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-04T15:14:10.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346880/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346880/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-05-27","Public Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of progress in eliminating the deficit between 2010 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","88"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346881","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-03","<p>We know that passengers are concerned about the cost of fares. That is why we have capped regulated fares at the level of the Retail Price Index (RPI) for two years running, and will continue to do so for the life of this parliament. It is also why over the past two years we have reduced the level of non-cumulative ‘flex’, by which operators could in each year increase individual regulated fares above the permitted average, from the 5% introduced by Labour to 2% in 2014 and 0% in 2015, and will continue this 0% policy to stop operators increasing individual fares above the now permitted average level of RPI for the life of this parliament. The fares rise for January 2016 will be based on July 2015’s RPI. The cost to the Government of capping regulated rail fares at RPI+0% for the next five years is estimated to be around £700m (in nominal prices).</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","95","2015-06-03T10:01:52.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346881/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346881/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-05-27","Railways: Fares","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will reduce rail fares in line with current levels of inflation.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","96"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346882","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-02","<p /> <p>The Government’s commitment to save £12bn from welfare spending was set out in its election manifesto. Further details will be given in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-02T13:51:23.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346882/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346882/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346882/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-05-27","Department for Work and Pensions: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, in what areas of his Department's expenditure spending reductions are planned.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","97"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346883","Department for Education","false","2015-06-02","<p>The cost of the new childcare entitlement of 30 hours per week for working families will be considered as part of the normal Budget and Spending Review process.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","174","2015-06-02T11:39:50.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346883/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346883/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-05-27","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the cost to the public purse of doubling the free childcare allowance for three and four year olds to 30 hours per week will be by 2020; and from which areas of departmental expenditure this will be funded.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","89"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346884","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-04","<p>In April 2015 Child Benefit rates were uprated by 1 per cent to £20.70 for the eldest or only child and to £13.70 for additional children.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-04T14:10:58.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346884/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346884/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-05-27","Child Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on maintaining current levels of child benefit.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","98"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346885","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-03","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-06-03T12:50:21.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346885/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346885/answer","PQ99.pdf","PQ99.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Zero Hour Contracts","ONS Letter to Member - Zero Hour Contracts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346885/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-05-27","Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many workers in the UK are on zero-hours contracts.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","99"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346886","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-03","<p>In the last five years there has been one report of inadvertent initiation of the weapon stowage compartment fog spray on Trident submarines.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-03T16:28:19.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346886/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346886/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-27","Trident Submarines: Fire Extinguishers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many formal reports his Department has received of firefighting fog sprays being activated in weapon stowage compartments on Trident submarines in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346887","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-04","<p>Strict safety rules govern the stowage of all flammable material on Trident submarines. These rules are regularly reviewed and compliance is subject to regular independent assessment.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-04T16:34:51.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346887/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346887/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-27","Trident Submarines: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what procedures exist to stop toilet rolls catching fire on Trident submarines; and what recent assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of any such procedures.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346888","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-02","<p>No reports of fighting between crew members on Trident submarines have been received since 2010.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-02T16:17:13.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346888/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/346888/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-05-27","Trident Submarines: Discipline","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what reports he has received since 2010 of fighting between crew members on Trident submarines.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","141"
